.SH NAME
drm_dp_dsc_sink_max_slice_count \- Get the max slice count supported by the DSC sink.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "u8" drm_dp_dsc_sink_max_slice_count
.BI "(const u8 dsc_dpcd[DP_DSC_RECEIVER_CAP_SIZE] "  ","
.BI "bool is_edp "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "dsc_dpcd" 12
DSC capabilities from DPCD
.IP "is_edp" 12
true if its eDP, false for DP
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Read the slice capabilities DPCD register from DSC sink to get
the maximum slice count supported. This is used to populate
the DSC parameters in the \fIstruct drm_dsc_config\fP by the driver.
Driver creates an infoframe using these parameters to populate
\fIstruct drm_dsc_pps_infoframe\fP. These are sent to the sink using DSC
infoframe using the helper function \fBdrm_dsc_pps_infoframe_pack\fP
.SH "RETURN"
Maximum slice count supported by DSC sink or 0 its invalid
